WEBVTT

00:02:32.440 --> 00:02:35.240
It's okay, Grandma.
If you can't remember, that's alright.

00:02:36.240 --> 00:02:39.600
That's just how Grandma is. Sometimes
she remembers, sometimes she doesn't.

00:02:39.680 --> 00:02:41.360
That's already more than enough.

00:02:41.440 --> 00:02:44.760
Some elders I've met at this age

00:02:44.840 --> 00:02:46.400
can barely remember anything at all.

00:02:48.040 --> 00:02:48.880
Oh.

00:02:51.840 --> 00:02:55.680
Grandma, could you please
take a look at these photos?

00:02:55.760 --> 00:02:59.480
Do you recognize anyone,
or remember anyone at all?

00:02:59.560 --> 00:03:02.520
If you do, please tell us.

00:03:06.560 --> 00:03:08.320
Oh.

00:03:10.240 --> 00:03:11.880
That's Mr. Wichan.

00:03:18.200 --> 00:03:21.040
And this woman's name is Ampha.

00:03:21.760 --> 00:03:23.240
She's pitiful.

00:03:24.240 --> 00:03:27.000
Her mother-in-law despised her.

00:03:27.640 --> 00:03:30.920
She and her child
were cast out of the house.

00:03:31.840 --> 00:03:34.960
Ah, no.

00:03:36.320 --> 00:03:39.960
Not cast out. They ran away.

00:03:41.200 --> 00:03:43.320
She's pitiful.

00:03:43.400 --> 00:03:45.880
She was accused of having an affair,

00:03:46.520 --> 00:03:50.000
so she ran away with Pong and Soi.

00:03:51.320 --> 00:03:55.360
Grandma, did Ms. Ampha
definitely have children?

00:03:55.440 --> 00:03:58.680
A boy or a girl? How many did she have?

00:03:59.280 --> 00:04:01.720
-Who?
-Ms. Ampha, Grandma.

00:04:02.320 --> 00:04:03.920
Who are you?

00:04:11.920 --> 00:04:14.400
Grandma. Grandma, do this.

00:04:15.960 --> 00:04:18.880
Once she starts weaving
the patterns she used to do regularly,

00:04:18.959 --> 00:04:21.600
her memory will come back. Just a moment.

00:04:21.680 --> 00:04:22.680
Oh.

00:04:22.760 --> 00:04:26.680
It's okay. We don't have to
trouble her that much.

00:04:26.760 --> 00:04:31.480
It's fine. It's brain exercise.
She usually does this all the time anyway.

00:04:50.520 --> 00:04:53.520
I'd say this is already a success.

00:04:54.680 --> 00:04:59.720
Yes. At least we learned that
Ms. Mysterious's real name is Ampha.

00:04:59.800 --> 00:05:01.560
It's a pity we couldn't ask everything.

00:05:01.640 --> 00:05:06.160
I even had photos of your mother,
Mr. Sarut, and Ms. Anong.

00:05:06.760 --> 00:05:09.400
There was also
a photo of Mr. Sarut's wife.

00:05:09.480 --> 00:05:12.320
I got them from your father's
hundred-day memorial album.

00:05:14.080 --> 00:05:15.520
So when are we coming back again?

00:05:16.200 --> 00:05:20.480
I think it'll have to be after we find out
where Ms. Ampha and her kid ran away to.

00:05:20.560 --> 00:05:23.040
And who they are, what their names are.

00:05:26.880 --> 00:05:31.360
She's pitiful.
She was accused of having an affair,

00:05:31.440 --> 00:05:35.440
so she ran away with Pong and Soi.

00:05:35.520 --> 00:05:37.000
I'm starting to be scared of you.

00:05:37.720 --> 00:05:39.400
You recorded it too?

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:43.760
Of course I did.
I'm a landscape architect, you know.

00:05:43.840 --> 00:05:47.840
It's part of my job to collect details.
I'm just adapting it a little.

00:05:47.920 --> 00:05:50.000
You're overreacting.

00:05:50.080 --> 00:05:52.720
I'm not overreacting. I'm impressed.

00:05:54.680 --> 00:05:55.960
Is that sarcasm again?

00:05:59.920 --> 00:06:03.640
Hey, I forgot to tell you something.

00:06:03.720 --> 00:06:05.000
Hm?

00:06:05.080 --> 00:06:06.640
I had a strange dream last night.

00:06:06.720 --> 00:06:08.000
What did you dream about?

00:06:09.360 --> 00:06:12.080
I dreamed that you and I…

00:06:16.480 --> 00:06:18.960
What's wrong? You choked?

00:06:19.960 --> 00:06:20.800
And…

00:06:21.600 --> 00:06:23.480
And… what did you dream about?

00:06:23.560 --> 00:06:26.400
I dreamed that you and I were just boxing.

00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:28.240
Huh?

00:06:51.800 --> 00:06:53.040
What's wrong with her?

00:07:00.720 --> 00:07:02.440
How is it? Can you walk comfortably?

00:07:04.920 --> 00:07:07.080
The cast feels a bit tight today.

00:07:07.160 --> 00:07:11.160
Well, we were in a hurry. By the time
I remembered, we were almost home already.

00:07:11.240 --> 00:07:14.360
Keep it down.
We're entering the house area now.

00:07:14.960 --> 00:07:16.680
But this is your house.

00:07:16.760 --> 00:07:19.800
This is the scariest
and most dangerous place of all.

00:07:19.880 --> 00:07:22.480
What's scary about it?
It's perfectly livable.

00:07:22.560 --> 00:07:26.840
Mr. Warat, can I sleep in today?
I'd like to take a little leave.

00:07:46.320 --> 00:07:48.840
Oh, another one. There, there.

00:08:09.880 --> 00:08:12.320
Enough already? I want to go inside.

00:08:21.280 --> 00:08:23.000
Why am I lying here?

00:08:27.360 --> 00:08:29.520
You lay down here yourself
and then forgot.

00:08:29.600 --> 00:08:31.960
Don't tell me you fell asleep.
You went completely quiet.

00:08:33.760 --> 00:08:35.320
I just saw a vision.

00:08:35.919 --> 00:08:37.000
Huh?

00:08:37.080 --> 00:08:42.600
I saw Ms. Mysterious, Ms. Ampha,
playing with her children.

00:08:43.200 --> 00:08:47.320
And she really does have two children.

00:08:47.400 --> 00:08:49.080
One boy and one girl.

00:08:49.160 --> 00:08:50.720
My child.

00:09:15.320 --> 00:09:17.720
Ms. Ampha, right?

00:09:18.600 --> 00:09:24.000
Yes. But I can't
communicate with her at all.

00:09:24.080 --> 00:09:26.760
Can you help me focus?

00:09:31.240 --> 00:09:34.920
Ms. Ampha, right now Mr. Warat and I

00:09:35.000 --> 00:09:37.160
have learned something about you.

00:09:37.880 --> 00:09:40.600
Could you please talk to us?

00:09:43.880 --> 00:09:48.120
Mr. Warat, Ms. Ampha looks sad again.

00:09:50.600 --> 00:09:51.760
Um…

00:09:53.040 --> 00:09:57.360
Ms. Ampha, if there's anything
you want us to help with,

00:09:57.440 --> 00:10:01.720
or anything you want us to do,
please tell us.

00:10:10.240 --> 00:10:13.280
Her form is becoming clearer.

00:10:13.360 --> 00:10:16.400
Should we stay still and listen?

00:10:19.760 --> 00:10:20.960
Please free me, my child.

00:10:22.520 --> 00:10:23.480
What?

00:10:25.320 --> 00:10:28.320
You're the mother of…

00:10:30.240 --> 00:10:31.720
What are you two doing?

00:10:35.880 --> 00:10:36.720
And what is this?

00:10:38.440 --> 00:10:42.200
Why aren't you talking inside the house?
So shameless.

00:10:42.800 --> 00:10:46.760
Well, Grandma, I'm not walking very well.

00:10:46.840 --> 00:10:50.360
Kluay was just supporting me.

00:10:50.440 --> 00:10:53.680
And holding arms like this is normal.

00:10:53.760 --> 00:10:56.360
We're a couple, after all.

00:10:57.000 --> 00:10:59.440
You're really talking back nonstop, Warat.

00:11:00.520 --> 00:11:01.440
Um…

00:11:02.520 --> 00:11:05.120
I think Warat must be tired.

00:11:05.200 --> 00:11:08.680
I'll take him inside now.

00:11:09.440 --> 00:11:10.400
Let's go.

00:11:11.160 --> 00:11:13.440
-Slowly.
-Ow, Kluay, gently. That hurts.

00:11:14.400 --> 00:11:15.680
Slowly.

00:11:20.000 --> 00:11:24.800
I thought that once Kluay came to live
in our house, everything would get better.

00:11:24.880 --> 00:11:27.880
But look. This is what it's like, Supol.

00:11:27.960 --> 00:11:30.080
With the utmost respect, ma'am…

00:11:30.160 --> 00:11:35.000
Stop. If you're going to defend them,

00:11:35.080 --> 00:11:36.720
then stop. I don't want to hear it.

00:11:36.800 --> 00:11:40.640
Earlier, did you hear
Ms. Kluay mention the name Ampha?

00:11:42.760 --> 00:11:43.760
What did you say?

00:11:43.840 --> 00:11:45.880
When we were walking from a distance,

00:11:45.960 --> 00:11:49.800
I saw Ms. Kluay and Mr. Warat talking,
as if they were speaking to someone.

00:11:50.400 --> 00:11:52.200
I thought I was just imagining things.

00:11:52.280 --> 00:11:55.760
But when I got closer, I clearly heard

00:11:55.840 --> 00:11:58.760
Ms. Kluay say the name Ampha.

00:12:03.840 --> 00:12:06.760
That's right.
I've been at the office all day.

00:12:06.840 --> 00:12:08.440
And where are you, Som?

00:12:09.040 --> 00:12:11.080
I'm at the office too.

00:12:11.160 --> 00:12:14.360
You've been at the office all day?

00:12:14.440 --> 00:12:17.640
Yes, all day. Where could I have gone?

00:12:17.720 --> 00:12:20.040
You know how busy I am.

00:12:20.120 --> 00:12:22.160
Mm, really?

00:12:22.240 --> 00:12:24.320
LEGAL MANAGER'S ROOM

00:12:28.800 --> 00:12:30.000
Come here.

00:12:30.080 --> 00:12:31.960
-Hey, ow!
-Hey.

00:12:34.880 --> 00:12:37.920
I already told you not to go
see Mom again, didn't I?

00:12:38.000 --> 00:12:40.760
Huh? How did you know?

00:12:40.840 --> 00:12:44.160
The place you went was my home.

00:12:44.240 --> 00:12:47.120
If I didn't know what was going on
in my own house, I'd be stupid.

00:12:48.560 --> 00:12:50.440
Okay, listen to me.

00:12:51.560 --> 00:12:55.160
Your mother is like my mother.
When she has problems,

00:12:55.240 --> 00:12:57.680
I have to go see her, right?

00:12:57.760 --> 00:13:00.480
But you promised you wouldn't go again.

00:13:00.560 --> 00:13:02.880
This time I was wrong. I'm sorry.

00:13:04.480 --> 00:13:07.240
And… how is Mom?

00:13:09.160 --> 00:13:10.840
Is there anything I can help?

00:13:11.920 --> 00:13:15.280
Really? You'll really help me?

00:13:15.880 --> 00:13:19.680
But Kluay must not know
that we're investigating her past.

00:13:20.280 --> 00:13:22.800
I'll handle it delicately.

00:13:24.000 --> 00:13:27.520
By the way, why did you come here?
Something happened, didn't it?

00:13:27.600 --> 00:13:30.880
Of course. I know now

00:13:30.960 --> 00:13:33.520
who was behind
staging the assault on Kluay.

00:13:34.520 --> 00:13:37.920
Ameena.
Even if Kluay doesn't press charges,

00:13:38.000 --> 00:13:41.080
I won't let it go.
I'll deal with her myself.

00:13:41.160 --> 00:13:45.200
Kluay was hurt and humiliated.
How could I just let it slide?

00:13:45.280 --> 00:13:47.680
A crazy girl like her
needs to meet someone crazier like me.

00:13:47.760 --> 00:13:49.920
This time, I'll deal with her for good.

00:13:50.000 --> 00:13:51.520
What are you going to do?

00:13:51.600 --> 00:13:56.440
Not just me. Us. You have to help me too.

00:13:56.520 --> 00:13:58.920
Wait. Really?

00:13:59.000 --> 00:14:01.800
-Mm. Let's go.
-Whoa, Som, wait.

00:14:01.880 --> 00:14:03.880
Why is it such a mess all day long?

00:14:03.960 --> 00:14:05.080
Ow.

00:14:12.720 --> 00:14:14.280
Um, Anong,

00:14:16.000 --> 00:14:17.720
this morning I saw Sin

00:14:17.800 --> 00:14:21.440
carrying a fruit basket
to give to Mrs. Wanee.

00:14:24.160 --> 00:14:25.280
Thank you so much.

00:14:26.840 --> 00:14:30.040
I'm just doing everything I promised you,

00:14:30.120 --> 00:14:32.840
to make sure everything goes smoothly.

00:14:32.920 --> 00:14:37.000
Actually,
Mr. Warat isn't seriously ill at all.

00:14:37.080 --> 00:14:40.760
But I thought it was a good opportunity
to let Sin show some goodwill.

00:14:40.840 --> 00:14:45.040
Honestly, if Sin could understand things
this easily, that would be great.

00:14:45.120 --> 00:14:47.440
Actually, he should've
understood this a long time ago.

00:14:49.600 --> 00:14:51.200
And there's one more thing.

00:14:52.120 --> 00:14:54.360
Sin doesn't fully believe yet, right,

00:14:54.440 --> 00:14:56.600
that I had something
to do with Wichan's death?

00:15:15.160 --> 00:15:20.760
CAMERA

00:15:23.840 --> 00:15:26.560
DR. MANOP NONTALAK
MR. WICHAN VANICH

00:15:42.960 --> 00:15:44.200
No.

00:15:48.320 --> 00:15:49.960
Mm, wait.

00:15:51.840 --> 00:15:54.600
Did Ms. Ampha speak to us
like she's our mom?

00:15:54.680 --> 00:15:59.200
Yes. But when your grandmother walked up
to us, she disappeared immediately.

00:15:59.280 --> 00:16:02.840
And I saw that moment,
you were communicating with her, right?

00:16:02.920 --> 00:16:06.800
I heard Ms. Ampha
say the words "my child."

00:16:07.400 --> 00:16:08.640
"My child."

00:16:09.840 --> 00:16:11.880
And she spoke like she was our mom?

00:16:12.680 --> 00:16:16.520
Or what your grandmother said
that Ms. Ampha is not your mother

00:16:17.280 --> 00:16:18.760
is not true?

00:16:19.520 --> 00:16:21.520
Then why would Grandma lie to me?

00:16:21.600 --> 00:16:24.280
And this woman's name is Ampha.

00:16:24.880 --> 00:16:29.560
Her mother-in-law despised her.
She's pitiful.

00:16:29.640 --> 00:16:32.160
She was accused of having an affair.

00:16:33.120 --> 00:16:34.600
Do you think…

00:16:37.240 --> 00:16:39.240
that I'm Ms. Ampha's child,

00:16:41.440 --> 00:16:43.360
and that Dad isn't really my father?

00:16:43.440 --> 00:16:46.920
Oh, I think we shouldn't
jump to conclusions just yet.

00:16:49.880 --> 00:16:52.400
If Ms. Ampha was not related to me,

00:16:54.320 --> 00:16:55.360
why does she keep following me?

00:16:58.680 --> 00:17:00.560
The affair Grandma Aom mentioned

00:17:01.280 --> 00:17:03.280
-could be my real father.
-Mm. Mm.

00:17:03.360 --> 00:17:06.400
You're imagining things again.

00:17:07.040 --> 00:17:09.480
You really should go
write a novel or something.

00:17:12.079 --> 00:17:12.920
Uh…

00:17:13.000 --> 00:17:15.240
I think we should go this way.

00:17:16.079 --> 00:17:17.800
-Come on.
-Hey, my leg hurts.

00:17:18.880 --> 00:17:21.480
I've checked the valve already.
It's still lacking.

00:17:21.560 --> 00:17:23.040
If we change the layout,

00:17:23.119 --> 00:17:26.119
I think we should add another
solenoid valve at one more point.

00:17:26.200 --> 00:17:28.840
I'll send you
the updated plan tomorrow, okay?

00:17:28.920 --> 00:17:32.880
Amazing. You dragged me here to work.

00:17:35.160 --> 00:17:36.960
Fantastic.

00:17:41.560 --> 00:17:45.320
You know, people can't stay stuck
on one thing all day long.

00:17:45.400 --> 00:17:46.840
It's not healthy.

00:17:47.400 --> 00:17:48.800
You're so diligent.

00:17:50.600 --> 00:17:52.440
Is this what you call diligent?

00:17:52.520 --> 00:17:55.320
I skipped work and helped you all night.

00:17:56.040 --> 00:18:01.160
I'm lucky I have a good team.
Otherwise, this wouldn't be finished.

00:18:03.400 --> 00:18:04.520
Diligent at causing trouble.

00:18:06.280 --> 00:18:08.600
Hey, why are you blaming me now?

00:18:10.560 --> 00:18:12.240
Speaking of which, this looks prettier.

00:18:14.960 --> 00:18:15.880
Me?

00:18:18.000 --> 00:18:18.840
The house.

00:18:22.680 --> 00:18:26.880
Hey, you could at least
pretend to compliment me a little.

00:18:30.040 --> 00:18:33.640
But it's good that your grandmother
decided not to tear the house down.

00:18:34.720 --> 00:18:35.760
Uh.

00:18:35.840 --> 00:18:40.800
Not tearing it down,
but throwing everything away instead.

00:18:42.120 --> 00:18:44.200
We're back to the same topic again.

00:18:46.400 --> 00:18:50.840
But the sky is beautiful tonight.
The stars are filling the sky.

00:18:52.440 --> 00:18:55.960
There, have you heard
of the Seven Sisters?

00:19:13.000 --> 00:19:14.160
Do you do this often?

00:19:15.440 --> 00:19:19.680
You mean stargazing?
Well… quite often, I guess.

00:19:19.760 --> 00:19:21.040
What a strange question.

00:19:23.120 --> 00:19:25.280
I mean inviting men to stargaze.

00:19:25.960 --> 00:19:27.080
Hey.

00:19:27.880 --> 00:19:28.880
Do you do that often?

00:19:29.680 --> 00:19:33.920
No. I usually look at the stars alone.

00:19:34.840 --> 00:19:38.160
You really have a lot of free time, huh?

00:19:38.240 --> 00:19:42.280
Sitting around watching stars. Pointless.

00:19:42.880 --> 00:19:45.440
Why are you criticizing people like that?

00:19:45.520 --> 00:19:51.160
Does it really take that much time,
just to look up and see the stars?

00:19:51.240 --> 00:19:53.760
It doesn't take much time. It's just…

00:19:53.840 --> 00:19:58.120
something suited for someone so free,
with nothing to do. Life is just

00:19:58.200 --> 00:20:01.160
-breathing, and looking at stars.
-Oh, okay, okay, okay.

00:20:01.240 --> 00:20:03.520
All right, I used the wrong words.

00:20:04.120 --> 00:20:09.760
I just can't believe there are people
who don't love nature at all.

00:20:09.840 --> 00:20:14.080
Yes, that's me. I don't love nature.

00:20:14.160 --> 00:20:19.560
I like air-conditioned rooms. I don't like
heat, sunlight, or mosquitoes.

00:20:20.360 --> 00:20:23.200
No one likes those things, but

00:20:23.280 --> 00:20:26.800
how can you not like nature?
Even Mr. Arnon said you like drawing.

00:20:30.000 --> 00:20:33.040
I like drawing, but not like…

00:20:34.360 --> 00:20:35.720
sitting around watching stars.

00:20:43.480 --> 00:20:44.360
Should we go home?

00:20:45.640 --> 00:20:49.080
I want to talk to Arnon about Grandma Aom.

00:20:49.920 --> 00:20:53.400
Take a short break, okay? It's fine.

00:20:53.480 --> 00:20:57.040
I'm exhausted. I fought a ghost all night.

00:20:57.720 --> 00:20:59.120
Fought a ghost?

00:21:02.600 --> 00:21:03.880
Nothing.

00:21:03.960 --> 00:21:07.440
Come on. If you want to go home,
let's go. I'll take you back myself.

00:21:09.200 --> 00:21:10.240
May I?

00:21:13.040 --> 00:21:15.560
Hurry up. Let's go.

00:21:17.840 --> 00:21:19.920
Did you do anything to me last night?

00:21:20.000 --> 00:21:22.440
Do what? We were in separate rooms.

00:21:22.520 --> 00:21:23.640
Mm. Really?

00:21:23.720 --> 00:21:25.120
Yeah.

00:21:25.200 --> 00:21:27.080
You don't have to know everything.

00:21:27.160 --> 00:21:28.280
Why are you blushing?

00:21:28.360 --> 00:21:31.640
What are you talking about? Walk properly.

00:21:39.320 --> 00:21:40.520
Did you see that?

00:21:42.960 --> 00:21:45.800
I didn't see it, but I heard it.

00:21:45.880 --> 00:21:50.800
I don't think it was a person.
It was probably a ghost.

00:21:50.880 --> 00:21:54.120
If it were a ghost,
I wouldn't be able to hear or see it.

00:21:54.840 --> 00:21:55.840
I think it was a thief.

00:21:55.920 --> 00:21:58.320
Uh…

00:21:59.200 --> 00:22:00.360
Uh.

00:22:01.280 --> 00:22:03.680
-Let's leave.
-No, let's check it out.

00:22:04.440 --> 00:22:05.280
No.

00:22:05.360 --> 00:22:06.400
Mm.

00:22:07.480 --> 00:22:10.000
-I'll go check.
-Hey.

00:22:35.880 --> 00:22:37.360
Come see me, my child.

00:22:44.880 --> 00:22:48.120
Mr. Warat. Mr. Warat, don't go.

00:22:50.000 --> 00:22:50.880
Mr. Warat.

00:22:53.320 --> 00:22:54.680
Mr. Warat, where are you going?

00:22:57.240 --> 00:22:59.000
Dad and Ms. Ampha are right here.

00:22:59.680 --> 00:23:02.480
That's not true. Get a grip.

00:23:13.080 --> 00:23:14.640
Mr. Warat, don't go in there.

00:23:15.680 --> 00:23:18.440
Mr. Warat, get a grip.

00:23:25.160 --> 00:23:26.680
Focus. Kluay, focus.

00:23:27.280 --> 00:23:29.280
Come see me, Warat.

00:23:29.360 --> 00:23:31.840
Ms. Ampha, please help.

00:23:45.640 --> 00:23:46.800
Mr. Warat

00:23:50.080 --> 00:23:51.360
You're back, right?

00:23:52.200 --> 00:23:53.200
What happened?

00:23:54.720 --> 00:23:55.920
Well…

00:24:01.080 --> 00:24:04.640
These are the fruits
that Mr. Sin brought yesterday, right?

00:24:04.720 --> 00:24:05.760
Yes, ma'am.

00:24:11.920 --> 00:24:15.200
Thank you so much, Supol,
for coming to see me so early.

00:24:16.520 --> 00:24:19.200
I couldn't sleep at all last night.

00:24:20.880 --> 00:24:26.040
If it weren't for you,
I wouldn't know who to talk to about this.

00:24:26.680 --> 00:24:29.920
With the utmost respect, ma'am,
please feel free

00:24:30.000 --> 00:24:34.360
to say everything.
Don't keep it bottled up inside.

00:24:34.440 --> 00:24:35.480
With respect.

00:24:36.080 --> 00:24:40.600
If Kluay really
can communicate with Ampha,

00:24:40.680 --> 00:24:42.840
what should we do next?

00:24:43.520 --> 00:24:46.560
More importantly,

00:24:46.640 --> 00:24:49.920
how much of the past can Warat handle?

00:24:50.000 --> 00:24:50.840
Ugh.

00:24:50.920 --> 00:24:52.440
I don't even want to think about it.

00:24:52.520 --> 00:24:57.120
From what I can tell,
it probably won't go that far.

00:24:57.200 --> 00:25:00.880
Because if Mr. Warat were going to know,
he would've known it back when Ms. Kluay

00:25:00.960 --> 00:25:02.440
fainted the last time.

00:25:02.520 --> 00:25:06.160
You mean, the day Kluay fainted,

00:25:06.240 --> 00:25:08.440
she saw Ampha?

00:25:08.520 --> 00:25:10.200
Yes, ma'am.

00:25:10.280 --> 00:25:12.520
That day, Ms. Som, Ms. Kluay's sister

00:25:12.600 --> 00:25:14.720
came to complain to us

00:25:14.800 --> 00:25:17.600
because her sister collapsed at the site.

00:25:17.680 --> 00:25:20.880
So I checked all the CCTV footage

00:25:20.960 --> 00:25:24.200
to confirm that her condition

00:25:24.280 --> 00:25:27.400
had nothing to do with us,
that we hadn't overworked her.

00:25:27.480 --> 00:25:28.920
And what did you see?

00:25:29.920 --> 00:25:34.240
What I saw was Ms. Kluay

00:25:34.320 --> 00:25:36.840
standing there, talking to empty air.

00:25:37.600 --> 00:25:38.560
Oh…

00:25:39.120 --> 00:25:42.200
I don't know whether
I made the right decision or not,

00:25:42.280 --> 00:25:45.200
letting Kluay stay in our house.

00:25:45.280 --> 00:25:46.720
Ma'am,

00:25:46.800 --> 00:25:49.920
the one Ms. Kluay was talking to
might not have been Ms. Ampha.

00:25:50.000 --> 00:25:53.240
And I'll find a way to prove it.

00:25:53.840 --> 00:25:56.080
Even if it's not Ampha,

00:25:56.160 --> 00:25:58.520
whether it's some spirit
or ghost of any kind,

00:25:58.600 --> 00:26:00.240
I'm not okay with it.

00:26:00.920 --> 00:26:02.080
Yes, ma'am.

00:26:24.560 --> 00:26:27.280
Hey, Grandma! Grandma, don't.

00:26:27.360 --> 00:26:28.600
-What? What?
-What?

00:26:29.360 --> 00:26:30.200
Hey!

00:26:30.800 --> 00:26:32.560
What are you doing, Boonsita?

00:26:44.640 --> 00:26:47.440
You will never be reborn again.
You're going to hell.

00:26:47.520 --> 00:26:50.000
Oh my goodness.
Why are you talking to me like this?

00:26:50.080 --> 00:26:53.640
This is getting
way too much now, Boonsita.

00:26:54.640 --> 00:26:58.360
I'm sorry, Grandma.
I wasn't talking to you, but…

00:26:58.440 --> 00:27:00.040
but I was talking to…

00:27:01.840 --> 00:27:03.360
Ugh.

00:27:03.440 --> 00:27:07.120
Please, can someone help
put all these fruits away?

00:27:07.200 --> 00:27:10.320
Fine. When everything's cleaned up,
you and I need to talk.

00:27:10.400 --> 00:27:11.920
Hey, anyone around here, come in.

00:27:15.480 --> 00:27:17.240
This is not your place.

00:27:18.480 --> 00:27:20.040
You want what happened
last night again or what?

00:27:25.280 --> 00:27:26.280
What happened?

00:27:27.360 --> 00:27:31.920
It's your girlfriend. Out of nowhere,
she stopped me from eating the fruit.

00:27:32.000 --> 00:27:35.920
These fruits are from the basket
Mr. Jirasin brought for you yesterday.

00:27:36.920 --> 00:27:38.880
So there's something in the fruit?

00:27:38.960 --> 00:27:41.400
What could there be?
She's just being paranoid.

00:27:41.480 --> 00:27:45.360
I know you and Sin don't really get along,

00:27:45.440 --> 00:27:48.960
but this is too much, Boonsita.

00:27:49.960 --> 00:27:53.720
Kluay, what did you see
in the fruit? Tell me.

00:27:56.200 --> 00:27:59.440
The ones we ran into last night
at the rose arbor house.

00:28:08.520 --> 00:28:10.800
Lamduan cookies, my favorite.

00:28:15.880 --> 00:28:17.840
Yours are on this side.

00:28:18.440 --> 00:28:21.480
And these are for Warat's family.

00:28:22.520 --> 00:28:24.640
Why fuss over them so much?

00:28:24.720 --> 00:28:28.240
I can't play the good guy too often.
Yesterday it was fruit, today it's sweets.

00:28:29.720 --> 00:28:32.280
Don't tell me
I have to offer these to them again.

00:28:33.080 --> 00:28:35.400
Offer what?

00:28:35.480 --> 00:28:37.800
Everything I do is for you, Sin.

00:28:40.360 --> 00:28:43.640
Oh, by the way, Sin. Yesterday,

00:28:43.720 --> 00:28:46.440
did you see them eat
the fruit you brought over or not?

00:28:47.160 --> 00:28:49.320
Auntie, I'm not going to
pester them like that.

00:28:49.400 --> 00:28:52.640
I dropped it off
and went straight to the office. Why?

00:28:54.680 --> 00:28:56.560
Just go to work.

00:28:57.320 --> 00:28:58.280
I'm going now.

00:29:19.840 --> 00:29:20.680
Follow me.

00:29:47.680 --> 00:29:50.920
Kluay, what did you see
in the fruit? Tell me.

00:29:51.600 --> 00:29:55.080
The ones we ran into last night
at the rose arbor house.

00:29:55.920 --> 00:29:57.160
Ghosts?

00:30:02.640 --> 00:30:03.560
Come in.

00:30:09.680 --> 00:30:11.480
-Excuse me, Mom.
-Mm.

00:30:11.560 --> 00:30:14.360
Um, are you busy right now?

00:30:14.440 --> 00:30:16.520
-No. Sit down.
-Thank you.

00:30:22.400 --> 00:30:25.320
I emailed you

00:30:25.400 --> 00:30:28.160
about Phuket. You received it, right?

00:30:28.760 --> 00:30:32.080
Oh, did you?
Sorry. I haven't opened it yet.

00:30:32.160 --> 00:30:36.920
Oh, no problem at all, Mom.
I came to bring you good news.

00:30:37.000 --> 00:30:38.680
We've successfully closed the deal

00:30:39.240 --> 00:30:43.200
for the Kata branch,
the hotel and the mall.

00:30:43.800 --> 00:30:46.640
Very good. That was fast.

00:30:46.720 --> 00:30:50.240
So I'll look at it now.
And did you call a meeting already?

00:30:50.320 --> 00:30:53.320
Not yet. I'm thinking of finalizing

00:30:53.400 --> 00:30:55.800
the Khon Kaen branch first,
then holding one meeting for everything.

00:30:55.880 --> 00:30:57.840
Khon Kaen?

00:30:57.920 --> 00:31:02.080
That's odd.
We only recently received the proposal

00:31:02.160 --> 00:31:04.680
to join that project.

00:31:04.760 --> 00:31:08.520
The Phuket group is also
interested in our Khon Kaen branch,

00:31:08.600 --> 00:31:10.880
so they sent another team over.

00:31:11.920 --> 00:31:13.680
Won't this

00:31:13.760 --> 00:31:16.640
be cutting in line too hard
against the original party?

00:31:17.280 --> 00:31:19.160
That's how business is these days.

00:31:19.240 --> 00:31:21.640
If you snooze, you lose.

00:31:21.720 --> 00:31:23.560
I think they'll understand.

00:31:24.320 --> 00:31:25.800
That's good.

00:31:27.400 --> 00:31:31.880
I was right to leave this in your care.

00:31:32.800 --> 00:31:34.080
Thank you, Sin.

00:31:40.680 --> 00:31:44.600
Ugh, walk slowly.
I can't keep up with you.

00:31:44.680 --> 00:31:46.000
Jirasin.

00:31:47.840 --> 00:31:51.280
He brought those fruits to my house,

00:31:51.360 --> 00:31:55.320
and still has the nerve to talk business.
He did it on purpose to mess with me.

00:31:55.400 --> 00:31:58.800
Calm down.
It might've just been a coincidence,

00:31:58.880 --> 00:32:02.440
like bad luck blowing in with the wind.

00:32:02.520 --> 00:32:07.560
It might've just been a ghost that
accidentally fell into Sin's fruit basket.

00:32:10.880 --> 00:32:12.920
Okay. Fine. I won't say anything.

00:32:13.000 --> 00:32:16.320
Do whatever you want, but don't forget,

00:32:16.400 --> 00:32:19.120
your leg's messed up.
Can you even fight him?

00:32:19.200 --> 00:32:22.760
If I can't, then I'll take this off
and throw it at his head.

00:32:26.280 --> 00:32:30.600
Hey, Mr. Arnon. Good you're here.
Help me deal with Jirasin.

00:32:31.280 --> 00:32:32.840
I'll see you in your office.

00:32:35.400 --> 00:32:36.240
Mr. Arnon.

00:32:36.320 --> 00:32:37.400
-Ouch!
-Ow! Sorry.

00:32:45.640 --> 00:32:48.200
This was found on Kluay
when she was brought in.

00:32:52.520 --> 00:32:54.160
Can you even walk, Arnon?

00:32:54.760 --> 00:32:57.960
-Are you old and going blind?
-Seriously. I almost died.

00:32:59.200 --> 00:33:00.280
What secret are you hiding?

00:33:03.040 --> 00:33:06.480
-What secret? There's no secret.
-None.

00:33:06.560 --> 00:33:09.200
Come to my office. Now.

00:33:21.760 --> 00:33:24.880
-Hey, Som. Oh? Som.
-Whoa.

00:33:25.520 --> 00:33:29.120
Huh? What?

00:33:31.560 --> 00:33:32.560
Here are the bank accounts.

00:33:32.640 --> 00:33:33.760
HEAD OF ENGINEERING ROOM

00:33:33.840 --> 00:33:37.280
All incoming accounts
are listed here in full detail.

00:33:37.360 --> 00:33:40.320
Every baht, every satang,
nothing slips through.

00:33:40.400 --> 00:33:43.400
You're actually very good
with money, aren't you?

00:33:43.480 --> 00:33:45.800
So why did you let
your debts pile up like this?

00:33:46.400 --> 00:33:50.800
It's bad luck. No matter
how good you are, you can still fall.

00:33:50.880 --> 00:33:52.560
But honestly,

00:33:52.640 --> 00:33:55.920
I like how you rotate the accounts.
It's tight.

00:33:56.000 --> 00:33:58.120
You have power in Vanich.

00:33:58.200 --> 00:34:00.960
I know every aspect of Vanich's finances.

00:34:01.960 --> 00:34:04.400
And I can plan the accounting for you too.

00:34:05.080 --> 00:34:10.040
There's nothing more perfect than this.
As long as we keep following this system,

00:34:10.120 --> 00:34:14.960
the information won't leak.
The Vanich family will never know

00:34:15.040 --> 00:34:16.360
who the foreign capital really is.

00:34:20.880 --> 00:34:21.719
What is it?

00:34:24.159 --> 00:34:27.320
Uh, the people
at the Vanich house refused it, sir.

00:34:31.400 --> 00:34:32.320
Why?

00:34:32.920 --> 00:34:35.120
A maid secretly told me

00:34:35.199 --> 00:34:39.080
they ordered the fruit you brought
yesterday to be thrown out.

00:34:48.639 --> 00:34:52.159
I don't believe Jirasin could close
the Khon Kaen and Phuket deals that fast.

00:34:52.239 --> 00:34:55.320
I'm trying to investigate
his connection trail.

00:34:55.400 --> 00:34:57.040
He's got nerve.

00:34:58.320 --> 00:35:02.400
He's deliberately announcing to us
that he has the power to do anything.

00:35:02.480 --> 00:35:06.800
If you're too slow,
I'll drag his guts out myself.

00:35:07.600 --> 00:35:12.280
Hey, why are you taking it out on me?
This takes time.

00:35:12.360 --> 00:35:14.920
They work very carefully.

00:35:15.000 --> 00:35:17.000
Nothing suspicious leaks out at all.

00:35:17.760 --> 00:35:19.160
That's why it takes time.

00:35:20.160 --> 00:35:21.920
Meaning you're giving him a chance

00:35:22.560 --> 00:35:25.200
to feed my grandmother something again?

00:35:25.720 --> 00:35:28.920
Do you know how hard it was for me

00:35:29.000 --> 00:35:32.520
to get rid of that stuff?
And my grandmother wouldn't believe me

00:35:32.600 --> 00:35:34.560
that it was ghost offerings.

00:35:35.240 --> 00:35:36.840
Why would he do that

00:35:36.920 --> 00:35:41.000
when Madam adores him so much?

00:35:41.080 --> 00:35:44.560
Because he's greedy.
Give him an inch, he'll take a mile.

00:35:44.640 --> 00:35:46.160
We have to stop him.

00:35:46.240 --> 00:35:50.240
Good thing you and Madam
have Ms. Kluay with you.

00:35:50.320 --> 00:35:54.440
That girl isn't stronger than ghosts.
She fights and then faints.

00:35:55.280 --> 00:35:56.920
I don't know if she can handle it.

00:35:57.000 --> 00:36:00.720
-I'm here. Sorry. The line was crazy long.
-Oh.

00:36:00.800 --> 00:36:04.240
Thank you. Actually,
my staff could've gone to buy it.

00:36:04.320 --> 00:36:05.560
It's fine.

00:36:05.640 --> 00:36:07.600
Here you go.

00:36:08.600 --> 00:36:11.840
No. I don't like this kind of coffee.

00:36:17.040 --> 00:36:21.400
You don't like this?
Then what kind of coffee do you like?

00:36:21.480 --> 00:36:26.640
I want to know where it's from,
what the shop is called.

00:36:27.640 --> 00:36:30.640
Oh, so you want something with brand.

00:36:30.720 --> 00:36:32.200
Just want to know where it's from.

00:36:34.200 --> 00:36:36.440
I was going to tell you earlier,

00:36:36.520 --> 00:36:39.400
but you had already disappeared.

00:36:39.480 --> 00:36:41.440
Keep going.
This is just a tiny part of him.

00:36:41.520 --> 00:36:44.360
It's okay. I'll drink this one myself.

00:36:45.480 --> 00:36:46.680
You won't be able to sleep.

00:36:46.760 --> 00:36:49.240
Come on, this coffee
can't do anything to me.

00:36:49.320 --> 00:36:53.160
I've been drinking strong coffee
since college. So I'm resistant, I guess.

00:36:56.080 --> 00:37:00.160
You already heard
what happened at the house, right?

00:37:00.240 --> 00:37:05.320
Yes. Next time, be more careful
about anything you accept from their side.

00:37:05.400 --> 00:37:08.880
Honestly, it'd be better
not to accept anything at all.

00:37:08.960 --> 00:37:11.760
But we probably can't, right?

00:37:11.840 --> 00:37:14.360
Let's talk about our matter first.

00:37:14.440 --> 00:37:17.960
How you two are going to
start with Grandma Aom's matter.

00:37:40.720 --> 00:37:46.080
WAKE UP, WORK, EXERCISE. HEALTH IS WEALTH.

00:37:51.440 --> 00:37:52.800
TRANSACTION COMPLETE

00:37:52.880 --> 00:37:54.440
AMOUNT: 10,000 BAHT

00:38:02.360 --> 00:38:05.440
It's because of you
that Jirasin keeps targeting Kluay.

00:38:05.520 --> 00:38:09.000
If Kluay is really innocent,
what is she afraid of?

00:38:09.080 --> 00:38:12.360
NEXT EPISODE

00:38:13.320 --> 00:38:15.040
I won't tolerate this anymore

00:38:15.120 --> 00:38:17.280
if Kluay still keeps rambling like this.

00:38:19.160 --> 00:38:21.000
Please don't do this, Ms. Ampha.

00:38:23.440 --> 00:38:24.680
Ampha?

00:38:26.640 --> 00:38:27.680
What happened?

00:38:29.200 --> 00:38:30.160
What did you see?

00:38:33.640 --> 00:38:35.920
Sin is about to face a serious accident.

00:38:37.280 --> 00:38:38.600
It could be fatal.

00:41:03.720 --> 00:41:05.600
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon